parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to lock or seize, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the coolant pump valve can cause coolant to leak onto the wiring harness, damaging electrical components and leading to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: loss of driving and braking control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag light to illuminate, and in some cases, the airbag may not deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
The failure of the PODS can cause the passenger airbag to malfunction, leading to increased risk of injury or loss of life in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The passenger airbag off light remains lit
the airbag monitoring light is illuminated
the passenger airbag does not deploy correctly
the system does not recognize the presence of a passenger

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning cruise control and auto-braking systems can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission coolant control valve leaks can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents or engine damage.

The failure of the transmission coolant control valve can cause coolant to leak into the transmission control module or wiring harness, leading to engine stalling, unexpected shutdown, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: especially at high speeds while highway driving
engine code P2753 - Valve for transmission fluid cooler circuit open

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coolant pump valve can cause coolant to leak onto the wiring harness, damaging or destroying multiple electrical components, leading to erratic vehicle behavior, loss of control, and potentially life-threatening situations.
